---
/**
 * transactions-isolation-fundamentals · Figure 2 — Level 1, the four ACID
 * promises (whose job is each letter).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/transactions-isolation-fundamentals.html (figure +
 * svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro component, NOT
 * inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG
 * that uses kebab-case attrs. No arrowhead markers are referenced here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The four ACID letters, each labelled with whose job it is: Atomicity and Isolation are the database, Durability is storage, Consistency is the application"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <g>
                <rect
                    x="14"
                    y="44"
                    width="138"
                    height="96"
                    rx="10"
                    fill="#f1eee2"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text
                    x="83"
                    y="68"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="15"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#7a1f12">A</text
                >
                <text
                    x="83"
                    y="86"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">Atomicity</text
                >
                <text x="83" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >all-or-nothing;</text
                >
                <text x="83" y="114" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >can I undo it?</text
                >
                <text
                    x="83"
                    y="131"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="8"
                    fill="#1f3a5a"
                    font-weight="700">DB · recovery</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="160" y="44" width="138" height="96" rx="10" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="229"
                    y="68"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="15"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#9a2417">C</text
                >
                <text
                    x="229"
                    y="86"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">Consistency</text
                >
                <text x="229" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >your invariants</text
                >
                <text x="229" y="114" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >hold (if code OK)</text
                >
                <text
                    x="229"
                    y="131"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="8"
                    fill="#9a2417"
                    font-weight="700">YOUR app, not DB</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect
                    x="306"
                    y="44"
                    width="138"
                    height="96"
                    rx="10"
                    fill="#f1eee2"
                    stroke="#7a1f12"
                    stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
                <text
                    x="375"
                    y="68"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="15"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#7a1f12">I</text
                >
                <text
                    x="375"
                    y="86"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">Isolation</text
                >
                <text x="375" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >concurrent txns</text
                >
                <text x="375" y="114" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >don't corrupt</text
                >
                <text
                    x="375"
                    y="131"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="8"
                    fill="#1f3a5a"
                    font-weight="700">DB · this whole book</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="452" y="44" width="134" height="96" rx="10" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="519"
                    y="68"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="15"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">D</text
                >
                <text
                    x="519"
                    y="86"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="10"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">Durability</text
                >
                <text x="519" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >committed data</text
                >
                <text x="519" y="114" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >survives a crash</text
                >
                <text
                    x="519"
                    y="131"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="8"
                    fill="#2f5d3a"
                    font-weight="700">storage · WAL+fsync</text
                >
            </g>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="28"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">ACID — Härder &amp; Reuter, 1983</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Only <tspan font-weight="700">I</tspan> is about more than one transaction at a time
                — which is exactly why it's hard.</text
            >
            <rect x="120" y="178" width="360" height="18" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text x="300" y="191" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >Atomicity + Durability share ONE mechanism: the write-ahead log (redo + undo)</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        "Atomic" means <em>abortable</em> — nothing to do with concurrency. Consistency is the odd letter
        out: it's your code's job, the DB only helps.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
